Difference between Java & Javascript:

1. Java is a strongly typed language whereas Javascript is lighted weighted language with easy syntax rules.
2. Java is object oriented programming language whereas Javascript is a object based programming.
3. Java can run on any virtual machine and web browser whereas Javascript run only on browser.
4. Objects of Java are class based even we cant make any program in Java without creating a class whereas Javascript objects are prototype based.
5. Java file is compiled and converted to source code to run whereas Javascript is compiled at run time by browsers engine.
6. Java is a standalone language whereas Javascript is a language which is integrated with its HTML elements.
7. Java uses more memory and Javascript uses less memory.
8. Java has a thread based approach towards concurrency whereas Javascript has event based approach towards concurrency.
